about.summary: The fit.models function and its associated methods (coefficients, print, summary, plot, etc.) were originally provided in the robust package to compare robustly and classically fitted model objects. The aim of the fit.models package is to separate this fitted model object comparison functionality from the robust package and to extend it to support fitting methods (e.g., classical, robust, Bayesian, regularized, etc.) more generally.

name: r-fit.models
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.5-14' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-fit.models
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  fn: fit.models_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/fit.models_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/fit.models/fit.models_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 93b9d119e97b36c648a19c891fc5e69f5306eb5b9bac16bf377555057afd4b6e

build:
  noarch: generic
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1003
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-lattice
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-lattice

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('fit.models')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('fit.models')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=fit.models
  license: GPL-2 and GPL-3
  summary: The fit.models function and its associated methods (coefficients, print, summary,
    plot, etc.) were originally provided in the robust package to compare robustly and
    classically fitted model objects. The aim of the fit.models package is to separate
    this fitted model object comparison functionality from the robust package and to
    extend it to support fitting methods (e.g., classical, robust, Bayesian, regularized,
    etc.) more generally.
  license_family: GPL
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - johanneskoester
    - bgruening
    - daler
    - jdblischak
    - cbrueffer
    - dbast
    - rvalieris
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.7.0
